===============================================================================
  PART II — DEFINITIONS
===============================================================================

§ 1. DEFINITIONS

  1.1  "Software" means the Neuro compiler, toolchain, standard library source,
       documentation, and all associated materials published at the official
       project repository or distributed by the Neuro Project Contributors.
       It does NOT include programs produced as output of the compiler.

  1.2  "Compiled Program" means any binary, object file, or other artifact
       produced by running the Neuro compiler over source code written by
       a third party. Compiled Programs are fully exempt from this License
       (see § 2.0).

  1.3  "Contributor" means any individual or legal entity that has submitted
       code, documentation, or other materials to the official Neuro project
       repository and whose contributions have been accepted and merged.

  1.4  "Derivative Work" means any work, whether in source or object form,
       that is based on or incorporates a substantial portion of the Software's
       protectable expression, as determined under applicable copyright law.
       For the avoidance of doubt, a work that merely interoperates with the
       Software through a published API, without incorporating its source code
       or protectable expression, is not a Derivative Work. Compiled Programs
       are never Derivative Works for purposes of this License.

  1.5  "AI System" means any artificial intelligence, machine learning model,
       large language model, neural network, or automated pipeline capable of
       parsing, analyzing, synthesizing, or generating source code or software
       architecture based on input material.

  1.6  "Competitive AI Reproduction" means the use of an AI System to process
       the Software's source code or documentation for the purpose of, and
       resulting in, the creation of a separate software product that directly
       competes with the Software in the same market category, where the output
       of the AI System constitutes a material portion of the competing
       product's codebase and such output was produced specifically from
       analysis of this Software. This definition requires both (a) a causal
       relationship between the AI processing of this Software and the
       resulting output, and (b) a direct competitive relationship between
       the products.

  1.7  "Personal Use" means use of the Software solely for an individual's
       own learning, research, experimentation, or non-commercial personal
       projects, with no distribution to third parties.

  1.8  "Internal Business Use" means use of the Software within an
       organization for that organization's own internal purposes, without
       distribution of the Software or Derivative Works to external parties,
       and without providing access to the Software's functionality as a
       service to external parties.

  1.9  "Commercial Distribution" means distributing the Software or a
       Derivative Work to external parties, whether for direct monetary
       compensation or as a material component of a product or service that
       generates revenue, including software-as-a-service offerings that
       expose the Software's compiler functionality to paying customers.
       This definition does NOT cover: (a) Compiled Programs; (b) tools
       or plugins that integrate with but do not redistribute the compiler.

  1.10 "You" or "Recipient" means any individual, organization, or legal
       entity that performs a copyright-regulated act with respect to the
       Software.

  1.11 "Corresponding Source" means the complete source code, build scripts,
       and all materials necessary to reproduce the distributed form of the
       Software or Derivative Work from the source.

  1.12 "Patent Claims" means any patent claims, now owned or hereafter
       acquired, that are necessarily infringed by a Contributor's
       contribution alone or by combination of that contribution with the
       Software to which the contribution was submitted.

