§ 2. COMPILED PROGRAM EXEMPTION (UNCONDITIONAL)

  Programs produced by compiling source code through the Neuro compiler are
  entirely outside the scope of this License. The Neuro Project makes no
  copyright claim over the output of its compiler. You may use, distribute,
  sell, and sublicense Compiled Programs under any terms you choose, without
  obligation to this License.

§ 3. RIGHTS GRANTED (FOR THE SOFTWARE ITSELF)

Subject to the conditions set forth in this License, the Neuro Project
Contributors hereby grant you the following rights:

  3.1  PERSONAL USE: You may use, study, run, and modify the Software for
       Personal Use (§ 1.8) without restriction beyond the conditions of
       this License.

  3.2  CONTRIBUTION: You may modify the Software and submit modifications as
       contributions to the official project repository, subject to § 11.
       Contributing to Neuro is encouraged and explicitly welcomed.

  3.3  NON-COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTION: You may distribute the Software or
       Derivative Works to third parties for non-commercial purposes, provided
       you satisfy all conditions of Part IV (Conditions).

  3.4  INTERNAL BUSINESS USE: Organizations may use the Software for Internal
       Business Use (§ 1.9) without a separate commercial license, provided
       they satisfy the attribution conditions of § 6.1 in any internal
       materials that reference the Software.

  3.5  TOOLING AND INTEGRATION: Tools, plugins, editor extensions, build system
       integrations, and other software that invoke or interoperate with the
       Neuro compiler but do not redistribute its source code or compiled form
       as a primary component are not subject to the Commercial Distribution
       restriction and may be distributed commercially under their own terms.

  3.6  COMMERCIAL DISTRIBUTION: You may distribute the Software or Derivative
       Works as part of Commercial Distribution (§ 1.10) provided that you
       satisfy all conditions of Part IV (Conditions), AND either:

         (a) Obtain a separate written Commercial Distribution License from
             the Neuro Project; or

         (b) Your commercial distribution is of a Derivative Work that
             constitutes a genuine independent fork under a distinct name
             per § 7, is fully source-available under this License or a
             compatible successor, and does not engage in Competitive AI
             Reproduction.

  No rights are granted beyond those explicitly stated in this § 3.

