§ 4. ALPHA STATUS DISCLOSURE

  4.1  Any distribution of the Software must include the Alpha Version Notice
       (Part I) verbatim and in a prominent, user-accessible location.

  4.2  All user-facing materials associated with a distribution of the
       unmodified Software must carry an unambiguous statement that the
       software is an alpha release.

  4.3  ALPHA NOTICE EXEMPTION FOR CERTIFIED DERIVATIVE WORKS: A Derivative
       Work distributed under a distinct name per § 7 is exempt from the
       requirement to carry the Alpha Version Notice if and only if ALL of
       the following conditions are met:

         (a) The Derivative Work has been independently tested and documented
             as suitable for its stated purpose by the distributing party;

         (b) The distributing party publishes a clear written certification
             statement identifying the specific version tested, the testing
             methodology employed, and the scope of warranted use;

         (c) The distributing party assumes liability for the accuracy of
             its own certification statement and for any warranties it
             extends to its own users in connection with the Derivative Work,
             and does not pass such liability back to the Neuro Project
             Contributors. Liability for defects in the upstream Software
             itself remains governed by §§ 14–15;

         (d) The Derivative Work is labeled as a "fork of Neuro" per § 6 and
             does not imply Neuro Project endorsement of the stability claim.

  4.4  You may not represent the unmodified Software to end users as
       production-ready or suitable for mission-critical use.

