APPLICABLE LAW.

§ 16. GOVERNING LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION

  16.1 Governing Law. This License shall be construed and enforced in
       accordance with the laws of Hungary, without regard to conflict-of-law
       provisions. Any legal action or proceeding arising under this License
       shall be brought exclusively in the courts located in Budapest, Hungary,
       and the parties hereby consent to personal jurisdiction and venue therein.

  16.2 Dispute Resolution. Any dispute arising out of or relating to this
       License that cannot be resolved informally within sixty (60) days of
       written notice shall be resolved by binding arbitration in accordance
       with the UNCITRAL Arbitration Rules in force at the time. The appointing
       authority shall be the Arbitration Court attached to the Hungarian Chamber
       of Commerce and Industry. The seat of arbitration shall be Budapest,
       Hungary. By default, proceedings shall be conducted entirely by written
       submission and video conference, without requiring travel by any party,
       unless a party demonstrates a specific need for in-person proceedings
       and the tribunal so directs. The language of the arbitration shall be
       English.

  16.3 Where mandatory local law renders arbitration unenforceable, disputes
       shall be resolved in the courts of the jurisdiction specified in § 16.1.

  16.4 Nothing in this License prevents either party from seeking emergency
       injunctive relief from a court of competent jurisdiction to prevent
       irreparable harm pending arbitration.

  16.5 Mandatory Local Law. Nothing in this § 16 deprives a Recipient who is
       a natural person of the protection of consumer-protection laws or other
       non-waivable mandatory provisions of the law of that Recipient's
       habitual residence. To the extent any such mandatory rule conflicts
       with the forum, choice-of-law, or arbitration provisions of this § 16,
       the mandatory rule prevails for that Recipient only, and the remaining
       provisions of this § 16 continue to apply to all other Recipients
       without modification.

§ 17. SEVERABILITY WITH FALLBACK HIERARCHY

  17.1 If any provision of this License is held unenforceable by a court of
       competent jurisdiction, that provision shall first be modified to the
       minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, preserving original
       intent to the maximum extent possible.

  17.2 If modification is not possible, the unenforceable provision shall be
       severed, and all remaining provisions shall continue in full force.

  17.3 In the specific case that the Competitive AI Reproduction restriction
       (§ 9.1) is found unenforceable as a contract term, the parties agree
       it shall be re-construed as a breach of confidence and unfair
       competition claim to the extent permitted by applicable law,
       preserving the Neuro Project's interest in protecting against the
       use of its source code as a primary input to AI-driven creation of
       directly competing products.

§ 18. ENTIRE AGREEMENT

  18.1 This License constitutes the entire agreement between the Neuro Project
       and the Recipient with respect to the Software and supersedes all prior
       agreements, representations, and understandings relating to the same.

  18.2 This License may be updated by the Neuro Project for future releases.
       The version of the License applicable to any given copy of the Software
       is the version that accompanied that specific copy at the time of its
       distribution. Recipients are not bound by updated versions unless they
